<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Four parts to this Quest.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
I. Turn in part<br>
II. Myga<br>
III. Dragonsbane Herb<br>
IV. Final Part<br>
V. Spell Info<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I. Turn In's</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Go to WW and find the Dragon Sage(Loc +2465, -4702) and talk to him. He will tell you about the Dragon age and Elder age. The key things to say to him to get it all are:<br>
<br>
Hail, The Dragon Sage<br>
who are you?<br>
what danger?<br>
what is the age of scale?<br>
what other gods?<br>
what is the elder age?<br>
what observations?<br>
what plant?<br>
<br>
At this point he will give you a coin called Giant Loyalist Token.<br>
<br>
Next, head to WL and find Tomekeeper Bjordnessin(Loc +665, -4586) and hand in the token to him. He will give you in return a Giant Scalebound Tome.<br>
<br>
Back to WW now. Turn in the Giant Scalebound Tome to the Dragon Sage and he will give you an Ornate Reagent Box, a 2-slot container.<br>
<br>
Step 1 Complete<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>II. Myga</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
This is the most difficult part of the quest. What you need is the Blood that drops off of Myga alone.  She is in a cycle with 4 other dragons that can pop.  Myga spawn's in front of ToV in WW and has a total of 4 PH's that can spawn in her place. There names are:<br>
<br>
Quoza<br>
Onava<br>
Gangel<br>
Amcilla<br>
<br>
The spawn time is 9 hours after one drop's. There is no pattern to Myga pop'ing, it is simply a 1 out of 5 chance it will be her.<br>
<br>
Best way to kill Myga or a PH is to be on the oposite wall from ToV and have it pulled to there. That is the best place with the least add's to do it with 1 group. If you get Myga that's great, pat yourself on the back, you are now done with the difficult part of the quest. Loot the Blood and your set.<br>
<br>
Step 2 Complete<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>III. Dragonsbane Herb</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Next, you get to head to Siren's Groto. Your targets are the Coldspine Seahorses. You must get the Dragonsbane Herb off of one of them and you are then done with the quest basically.<br>
<br>
Step 3 Complete<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>IV. Final Part</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Now, take the Blood from Myga and the Herb and put them into the Ornate Reagent Box you got earlier. Hit combine and you will now have a Sealed Reagent Box. Go back to the Dragon Sage in WW and hand him the new box.<br>
Congradulations. You are now the proud owner of Porlo's Furry...i.e. Dragon's Bane<br>
<br>
Step 4 Complete<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Note:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
* The Dragon Sage is not on any faction and will talk to anyone.<br>
** The Giant in WL can be charmed for his turn in part if your on Dragon faction.<br>
***Would suggest doing steps in the order of 2,3,1,4<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>V. Spell Info</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Porlo's Fury<br>
Wizard of the 60th level spell.<br>
Reagent's used: 2 Peridot's per cast<br>
Dragon's it can be used on: Specific Type's of Dragons that are on Yelinak Faction<br>
Damage: 2,000 Direct Damage Spell that will NEVER be resisted no matter what nor no matter the difficulty of the mob.<br>
Cast Time: 6 Seconds<br>
Recast Delay: 2.5 Seconds<br>
Mana Used: 450<br>
Ratio: Mana / Damage = .225<br>
